    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tuned In to Cable And Grateful for It</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Greg J Gibson letter on August 20 Soapbox essay lauds availability of cable television (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to ''Cable Gal: A Former TV Snob Lets a Hundred Channels Bloom'' (Soapbox, Aug. 20):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to ''Cable Gal: A Former TV Snob Lets a Hundred Channels Bloom'' (Soapbox, Aug. 20):</p>
        <p>I am a semi-homebound person who watches those hundred channels. When you can't fit, as a fat person, in a movie theater seat or go outdoors, you are lucky to have cable television. Cable is costly, but for those who can afford it, it is worth it for the movie and pay-per-view channels; at least there is no one talking.</p>
        <p>GREG J. GIBSON  Somerville</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
